import os

def extract_year_from_filename(filename):
    # Extract the base name of the file (e.g., 'Penalties_2015.csv')
    base_name = os.path.basename(filename)
    # Split the base name by '_' and take the second part ('2015.csv'), then split by '.' and take the first part ('2015')
    year_str = base_name.split('_')[1].split('.')[0]
    # Convert the year string to an integer
    return int(year_str)

# Assuming your DataFrames are correctly loaded
dfpen2015['Year'] = extract_year_from_filename('/content/Penalties_2015.csv')
dfpen2016['Year'] = extract_year_from_filename('/content/Penalties_2016.csv')
dfpen2017['Year'] = extract_year_from_filename('/content/Penalties_2017.csv')

import os

def extract_year_from_filename(filename):
    # The year is the second element when splitting by '_', so index should be 1
    return int(os.path.basename(filename).split('_')[1].split('.')[0])

performancedf2015['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2015.csv')
performancedf2016['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2016.csv')
performancedf2017['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2017.csv')
performancedf2018['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2018.csv')
performancedf2019['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2019.csv')
performancedf2020['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2020.csv')
performancedf2021['FILEDATE']= extract_year_from_filename('/content/QualityMsrMDS_2021.csv')

combinedperformance_df=pd.concat([performancedf2015,performancedf2016,performancedf2017,performancedf2018,performancedf2019,performancedf2020,performancedf2021], ignore_index=True)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a new column for quarter
combinedperformance_df['Quarter'] = combinedperformance_df.apply(
    lambda x: 'Q1' if pd.notnull(x['Q1_MEASURE_SCORE']) else (
              'Q2' if pd.notnull(x['Q2_MEASURE_SCORE']) else (
              'Q3' if pd.notnull(x['Q3_MEASURE_SCORE']) else 'Q4')), axis=1)

# Melt the DataFrame to have quarters and scores in separate rows
melted_df = pd.melt(combinedperformance_df, id_vars=['FILEDATE', 'Quarter'],
                    value_vars=['Q1_MEASURE_SCORE', 'Q2_MEASURE_SCORE', 'Q3_MEASURE_SCORE', 'Q4_MEASURE_SCORE'],
                    var_name='Quarter_Var', value_name='Score')

# Filter out null scores
melted_df = melted_df[melted_df['Score'].notnull()]

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))
sns.barplot(data=melted_df, x='Quarter', y='Score', hue='FILEDATE', palette='viridis')
plt.title('Quarterly Measure Scores by Year')
plt.xlabel('Quarter')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.legend(title='Year')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Group by STATE and FILEDATE, then calculate the mean for each quarter
grouped = combinedperformance_df.groupby(['STATE', 'FILEDATE']).agg({
    'Q1_MEASURE_SCORE': 'mean',
    'Q2_MEASURE_SCORE': 'mean',
    'Q3_MEASURE_SCORE': 'mean',
    'Q4_MEASURE_SCORE': 'mean'
}).reset_index()

# Melt the DataFrame to prepare for visualization
melted = pd.melt(grouped, id_vars=['STATE', 'FILEDATE'], var_name='Quarter', value_name='Avg_Score')

# Visualizing the data with a bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.barplot(data=melted, x='Quarter', y='Avg_Score', hue='STATE', ci=None, palette='muted')
plt.title('State Comparison of Average Performance per Quarter')
plt.xlabel('Quarter')
plt.ylabel('Average Score')
plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()  # Adjust layout to make room for the legend
plt.show()
